<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Anderson Lee Has Implants Removed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Former ``Baywatch'' star Pamela Anderson Lee  
has had her breast implants removed. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's something I've been wanting to do for a long time and I'm  
very happy with my decision,'' Ms. Lee said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Surgery on the 31-year-old actress, now appearing in the  
syndicated show ``V.I.P.,'' was performed last week in Los Angeles, 
said Ms. Lee's spokeswoman Marleah Leslie. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Leslie said Ms. Lee had no problems with the implants and is  
not worried her smaller figure will hurt her modeling career or 
chances in landing future acting roles. 
</P>
<P>
	``If she was, she wouldn't have done it,'' Ms. Leslie told USA  
Today. ``She just wanted her body to go back to its natural 
state.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
