<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Whooping Cranes Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- In an April 13 story on whooping  
cranes producing the first eggs in the wild in decades, The 
Associated Press erroneously attributed a quote to George 
Archibald, director of the International Crane Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
	It was biologist Marty Folk who made this statement: ``We'll be  
happy if the eggs hatch, and we'll be really happy if they do raise 
these chicks. ... But we don't really expect it to happen.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
