<HEADLINE> Wild Heart Dancing Wins in Kentucky </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- Taking the early lead, Wild Heart Dancing  
wasn't headed Thursday and posted a narrow victory in the $111,100 
Palisades Stakes at Keeneland. 
</P>
<P>
	Wild Heart Dancing, with Jorge Chavez up, ran 1 1/8 miles over turf  
in 1:49 3-5 and finished a neck in front of Riviera Colleen. It was 
three-quarters of a length back to third-place Suffragette in the 
field of nine 3-year-old fillies. 
</P>
<P>
	Pico Teneriffe, the 6-5 favorite who was seeking a third  
straight victory, stumbled on the turn and finished seventh. 
</P>
<P>
	Wild Heart Dancing, owned by Robert Firth's My Jo Lee Stable,  
paid $16.80, $8.60 and $4.80. Riviera Colleen returned $6.40 and 
$5, while Suffragettte paid $12.20. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the fifth victory in 13 lifetime starts for Wild Heart  
Dancing, who received $68,882, increasing her career earnings to 
$191,341. 
