<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fusion 2, Burn 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Diego Serna scored a late tying  
goal and Jeff Cassar made three saves in the shootout as the Miami 
Fusion rallied for a 2-1 victory over the Dallas Burn on Thursday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
	Miami won the shootout 3-0 as Henry Gutierrez, Jay Heaps and Leo  
Cullen scored on Dallas goalkeeper Matt Jordan. Cassar saved 
attempts by the Burn's Brian Haynes, Temoc Suarez and Mickey 
Trotman. 
</P>
<P>
	The Fusion, which had lost its previous two matches by 4-1  
scores, won despite the absence of star midfielder Carlos 
Valderrama. The veteran midfielder has been benched indefinitely by 
coach Ivo Wortmann. 
</P>
<P>
	The win capped a contentious week for Wortmann, who told  
Valderrama that he doesn't fit Miami's system of play. 
</P>
<P>
	With Valderrama out, Wortmann's starting lineup had four rookies  
and three second-year players. The Fusion got even younger in the 
25th minute when second-year forward Jason Boyce replaced Brazilian 
forward Roberto Gaucho, who left the game with an injured shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas played the final 47 minutes with 10 men after captain  
Richard Farrer was given a red card by referee Robert Sheker for a 
hard slide tackle on Miami's Nelson Vargas. 
</P>
<P>
	Until Serna's goal in the 74th minute, the Fusion's inexperience  
proved to be a bigger shortcoming than the Burn's one-man deficit. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas took a 1-0 lead in the 58th minute when Dante Washington  
scored on a breakaway against Cassar after beating Miami's offside 
trap. Fusion rookie defender Jeremy Aldrich failed to push up on 
the trap, leaving Washington onside to receive a cross from Haynes. 
</P>
<P>
	Serna equalized for Miami 16 minutes later when he headed Henry  
Gutierrez's free kick into the far netting. The goal was the first 
allowed by Dallas this season, and broke a 402-minute scoreless 
streak by the Burn dating to last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
