<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Calvin Klein Candles Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- About 35,000 fragranced candles are being  
recalled because they may burn with high flames that could pose 
fire hazards, the U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Calvin Klein Cosmetics Co. recalled the candles after getting  
eight reports from consumers about higher-than-normal flames. One 
person ported a minor burn injury, the CPSC said. 
</P>
<P>
	The recalled candles come in two sizes -- 2 1/4 inches and 1 1/2 inches  
high -- and were packaged in tin containers of various colors. The 
larger candles were sold individually and in gift sets. The smaller 
candles were given away as samples, gifts and included in gift 
sets. 
</P>
<P>
	Specialty and major department stores sold the candles from July  
1998 until recently. Consumers who have them should cease using 
them immediately and return the items to the store where they were 
purchased. 
</P>
<P>
	The fragrances of the recalled candles are: Obsession, Obsession  
for Men, Eternity, Eternity for Men, Escape, Escape for men, 
Contradiction, CK One and CK Be. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
