<HEADLINE> Treasury Bond Prices Fall / Bonds  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Treasury bond prices were falling at midday and  
short-term interest rates were mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The price of the Treasury's main 30-year bond was down 5/16  
point, or $3.13 per $1,000 in face value, around midday, while its 
yield rose to 5.53 percent from 5.51 percent late Wednesday. Prices 
and yields move in opposite directions. 
</P>
<P>
	Yields on three-month Treasury bills were 4.26 percent as the  
discount fell 0.01 percentage point from late Wednesday to 4.16 
percent. Six-month yields were 4.50 percent as the discount rose 
0.01 percentage point to 4.34 percent. One-year yields were 4.64 
percent as the discount rose 0.02 point to 4.43 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Yields are the interest bonds pay by maturity, while the  
discount is the interest at which they are sold. 
</P>
