<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Mixed; Gold Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in late afternoon trading in Europe today. Gold prices 
were lower. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0759, down from $1.0791 Wednesday. The  
dollar was quoted at 118.75 Japanese yen, up from 118.81 yen. At 
midday in New York, the euro was quoted at $1.0724 and the dollar 
was quoted at 118.79 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Wednesday:  
1.4894 Swiss francs, up from 1.4865; 1.4892 Canadian dollars, down 
from 1.4939. The British pound was quoted at $1.6130, down from 
$1.6175. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, but are locked at constant rates against 
the euro. Based on euro rates, the dollar is worth: 1.8179 German 
marks, up from 1.8125; 6.0968 French francs, up from 6.0787; 2.0482 
Dutch guilders, up from 2.0422; 1,799.67 Italian lire, up from 
1,794.34. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $282.20 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$282.70 on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $282.65, down from $282.95.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold fell $1.70 in Hong Kong to $282.05.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $4.98 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$4.93. 
</P>
</TEXT>
