<HEADLINE> NATO Confirms Convoy Strikes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) -- NATO confirmed today that allied  
aircraft struck two convoys in Kosovo, one military and one mixed 
of military and civilians, and that at least one civilian tractor 
was hit. 
</P>
<P>
	A NATO officer, speaking on condition of anonymity, said there  
were two convoys on the same road. Two NATO planes attacked -- one 
hit the military convoy, the other struck at what he called a 
``mixed convoy.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The officer said NATO is still studying what happened, but that  
evidence appeared to show a tractor hit in the second convoy. 
</P>
<P>
	All manned NATO planes returned to base safely from overnight  
attacks, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	NATO spokesman Jamie Shea said there still were few details.  
</P>
<P>
	``We haven't excluded any option, and we are continuing to  
investigate,'' Shea said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
