<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Angels' Vaughn Might Return Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Mo Vaughn, who sprained his ankle two  
batters into his first game with the Anaheim Angels, could rejoin 
the team within a week. 
</P>
<P>
	Dr. Lewis Yocum examined Vaughn on Thursday and said the first  
baseman's ankle had improved. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was very pleased with Mo's progress and the prognosis is  
very favorable,'' said Yocum, the Angels' medical director. ``Mo 
has done a lot of rehab work since suffering the injury. 
</P>
<P>
	``The possibility of his return within the week is optimistic,  
but definitely reasonable.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Vaughn, who signed an $80 million, six-year free agent contract  
with the Angels over the winter, sprained his left ankle when he 
fell into the Cleveland dugout chasing a foul pop in the season 
opener. 
</P>
<P>
	He was placed on the 15-day DL on April 9, just the second time  
on the injured list in his nine-year career. 
</P>
<P>
	Also Thursday, Yocum examined center fielder Jim Edmonds, who is  
on the DL with a sore right shoulder. There was no indication of 
when he might rejoin the team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
