<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Radio's Mancow To Join Fox News </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Mancow Muller, a controversial radio personality  
who once tied up traffic on the Golden Gate Bridge to give a 
colleague a haircut, is joining Fox News Channel's morning team. 
</P>
<P>
	The syndicated radio host will give news commentaries during  
``Fox and Friends'' through cameras placed in his Chicago radio 
studio. 
</P>
<P>
	``Mancow's attitude and non-conventional views fit perfectly  
with the spirit of `Fox and Friends,''' said Chet Collier, senior 
vice president of Fox News Channel, on Wednesday. 
</P>
