<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Unisys Profit Almost Doubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BLUE BELL, Pa. (AP) -- Unisys Corp. nearly doubled its  
first-quarter profit and easily beat Wall Street predictions, 
helped by strong demand for the company's computer services and big 
business machines. 
</P>
<P>
	Unisys reported on Thursday that it earned $111.2 million, or 32  
cents a share in the three months ended March 31. That was up from 
a profit of $62.7 million, or 14 cents a share, in the year-ago 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Revenue grew 10 percent to $1.81 billion from $1.65 billion.  
</P>
<P>
	The profit greatly exceeded the 24 cents a share expected by  
analysts surveyed by First Call. Unisys stock closed down 31 1/4 cents 
at $29 in trading on the New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	Unisys partly cited strong sales of business computers called  
servers, which run networks of smaller machines, saying that more 
customers needed powerful computers to handle Internet 
transactions. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawrence Weinbach, Unisys' chief executive officer hired in  
September 1997, is overseeing a shift at the company from computer 
manufacturing to computer services. Unisys employs 33,200 people. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
