<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Accused of Long-Haired Stalking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAYLOR, Mich. (AP) -- A man with an apparent hair fetish was  
accused of stalking a long-haired 7-year-old girl and trying to 
break into her family's home in an attempt to cut off her locks. 
</P>
<P>
	Mark Philip Thackery, 46, was in jail on $100,000 bond, charged  
with stalking a minor and attempted home invasion. 
</P>
<P>
	The suspect approached the girl's mother at a garage sale at the  
family's home last July and offered her $100 for the girl's 
ponytail, Sgt. Jeff Turner said. 
</P>
<P>
	``She, of course, freaked out and shooed him away,'' Turner  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	After that, the family -- whose name was withheld to protect the  
child -- reported seeing the man parked near their home at least 
seven times. 
</P>
<P>
	On April 7, the girl's father was in his car when he noticed a  
man trying to open the front door to their home. His wife and 
daughter, who were inside, called police while the father 
confronted the man, who then left. 
</P>
<P>
	That evening, police arrested Thackery, who is being held  
pending an April 28 preliminary hearing. 
</P>
<P>
	Stalking a minor carries a penalty of up to five years in  
prison. Attempted home invasion is punishable by up to 10 years in 
prison and a $10,000 fine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
