<HEADLINE> Deadly Storms Hit Mississippi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Powerful storms rolled across the South early today after  
damaging homes and downing power lines in southeastern Mississippi. 
One person was killed and more than two dozen were injured, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials at South Central Regional hospital in Laurel said  
early today that they had treated 25 to 30 people for cuts suffered 
in Wednesday night's storms. Laurel is 30 miles north of 
Hattiesburg. 
</P>
<P>
	A 71-year-old man was killed near Soso, according to Jones  
County authorities, but no details were immediately available. The 
storms were accompanied by very strong winds. 
</P>
<P>
	Heavy rain and windy conditions were reported throughout  
Mississippi, but the majority of the damage appeared to be in 
northern Jones County and southern Jasper County, a region about 60 
miles southeast of Jackson. 
</P>
<P>
	A Jones County sheriff's dispatcher said deputies going into  
storm-damaged areas reported numerous downed trees and power lines 
and widespread damage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
