<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tampa Puts Alvarez on Disabled List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Devil Rays placed pitcher Wilson  
Alvarez on the 15-day disabled list Thursday with inflamation in 
his left shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Alvarez, who signed a $35 million, five-year contract before  
last season, missed six weeks with tendinitis in his rotator cuff 
last year. The left-hander is 6-15 since signing the contract. 
</P>
<P>
	While throwing in-between starts on Wednesday, Alvarez said he  
felt a twinge in his shoulder. He threw Thursday to see test it but 
immediately felt a pop. 
</P>
<P>
	``I can't even raise my arm now,'' Alveraz said. ``Its  
painful.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Trainer Jamie Reed said the injury is not serious, but Alvarez  
will get a second opinion when the team returns to Tampa next week. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's frustrating because I want to show these people I can do  
the job,'' Alvarez said. 
</P>
<P>
	The move was retroactive to April 12.  
</P>
</TEXT>
