<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rojohn Wins 1 Meter Diving National </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Michelle Rojohn on Thursday held off  
Rachelle Smith and Erica Sorgi in the women's 1-meter event to win 
the first final of the U.S. Spring National Championships. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the first national victory for Rojohn, whose highest  
previous finish was second in the 1997 Spring Nationals. 
</P>
<P>
	``I knew I was hungry. I think there's more pressure if you had  
won before and everybody is viewing you as a favorite,'' Rojohn 
said. ``It's great to be an underdog. I surprised myself with the 
win.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rojohn earned a spot on the national team, joining Smith, Sorgi  
and Jenny Lingamfelter. 
</P>
<P>
	Jenny Keim placed first in the quarterfinals and semifinals, but  
finished fifth, one spot shy of a national team berth. 
</P>
<P>
	In the men's platform semifinals, Mark Ruiz distanced himself  
from the competition, following up a top qualifying finish in the 
quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
	Ruiz, diving before his home crowd, was awarded the first  
perfect 10 score of the competition in the quarters, then followed 
with another in the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is my best event. I treat the preliminaries like a  
practice round, so I just went out and relaxed and did my thing,'' 
Ruiz said. ``It did surprise me that I ended up so far ahead, but 
the overall goal was to get into the finals.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Justin Dumais qualified second, more than 36 points behind  
Ruiz's 659.07. Troy Dumais qualified fourth, just behind David 
Pichler, who placed first in the 3-meter preliminaries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
